00:07:19.374 --> 00:07:21.040
So it's like we didn't
cross the border,

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:22.480
the borders crossed
us type of thing.

00:07:22.480 --> 00:07:23.646
MARGARET GARCIA: Absolutely.

00:07:23.646 --> 00:07:26.415
MARCUS GRIMALDO: And he married
my grandmother Guadalupe who--

00:07:26.415 --> 00:07:28.040
you want to tell us
a little bit about?

00:07:28.040 --> 00:07:29.456
You touched upon
her a little bit.

00:07:29.456 --> 00:07:31.070
But when I was
reading your story,

00:07:31.070 --> 00:07:32.930
that hit home for me because--

00:07:32.930 --> 00:07:35.840
God rest her soul-- but yeah,
who is Guadalupe to you?

00:07:35.840 --> 00:07:38.510
MARGARET GARCIA: My
grandmother adopted

00:07:38.510 --> 00:07:41.660
a little girl named Guadalupe.

00:07:41.660 --> 00:07:44.750
And she died of
tuberculosis of the bone

00:07:44.750 --> 00:07:49.610
in the communicable diseases
ward at the general hospital.

00:07:49.610 --> 00:07:52.280
And then she found
my father again

00:07:52.280 --> 00:07:54.470
and he came back to
live with her after he

00:07:54.470 --> 00:07:56.280
was being raised in Sonora.

00:07:56.280 --> 00:07:58.190
And my mother came--

00:07:58.190 --> 00:08:01.220
illegally, she crossed.

00:08:01.220 --> 00:08:04.610
And my grandmother
was a bit of a coyote,

00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:07.590
and so what she did
was she gave my mother

00:08:07.590 --> 00:08:09.830
those papers that showed--

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:12.310
so she was using
Guadalupe's papers.

00:08:12.310 --> 00:08:16.380
So when I was born, the name
on the birth certificate

00:08:16.380 --> 00:08:22.250
said Guadalupe, so I have a
two-page birth certificate

00:08:22.250 --> 00:08:23.120
that corrected that.

00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:25.290
We went and we corrected
all that stuff.

00:08:25.290 --> 00:08:27.420
And my mother became
an American citizen.

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:29.510
