00:10:26.369 --> 00:10:28.910
MARGARET GARCIA: It was in the
'30s, but what was interesting

00:10:28.910 --> 00:10:32.540
with my uncle who was
repatriated, born here,

00:10:32.540 --> 00:10:34.190
his mother was here--

00:10:34.190 --> 00:10:37.790
he goes down to Mexico and he
says, the only thing I wanted

00:10:37.790 --> 00:10:39.650
was to get an education.

00:10:39.650 --> 00:10:42.360
All I wanted was an education.

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:44.720
So he goes to the Mexican
schools down there

00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:46.430
and they say, oh, no.

00:10:46.430 --> 00:10:47.300
You're an American.

00:10:47.300 --> 00:10:49.430
You have an American
birth certificate.

00:10:49.430 --> 00:10:54.710
We won't let you take the
place of another Mexican child.

00:10:54.710 --> 00:10:56.300
So they wouldn't
educate him here

00:10:56.300 --> 00:10:58.590
and they yanked him
out of school there.

00:10:58.590 --> 00:11:01.160
